1. Game Overview
Hell Inc. — The Intern is a 2D top-down comedy social strategy game where the player takes the role of a brand new intern at Hell Incorporated, assigned to a small quirky town to collect souls and meet their quarterly quota. Progress happens not through combat but through conversation — identify each resident's deepest desire and get them to sign on the dotted line.
The game uses a dual-view system: a top-down overworld for exploration and planning, and a first-person encounter view for dialogue — powered by the Claude AI API which plays each NPC and evaluates whether the player's pitch is convincing enough to close the deal.
The tone is office comedy with dark edges. Think The Office meets Beetlejuice. The horror is not monsters — it is paperwork, rejection rates, and a micromanaging boss who will not stop sending messages about your close rate.


2. Core Game Loop
The Loop
Explore the town top-down, observe residents, and gather intel on their desires
Approach a house and knock — view switches to first-person encounter mode
Engage the resident in conversation, identify their hidden desire, and pitch a soul acquisition package
The AI evaluates whether the player's dialogue matches the resident's vulnerability
If successful, the deal is signed, the town begins to change, and your quota inches closer
Hit your quota without getting exposed or fired — no timer, just skill and strategy

Win / Lose
Outcome
Condition
WIN
Reach soul quota — Gary sends a congratulatory message and you are promoted to Junior Demon
LOSE — Fired
Rejection rate gets too high — Gary pulls you from the assignment for embarrassing Hell Inc.
LOSE — Exposed
