9. MVC Architecture
Model
World state — all NPC states, suspicion meter, soul count, quota, rejection rate tracker
NPC data — personality profiles, hidden desires, current state, conversation history
Deal system — active packages, ripple effect queue, soul value tracking
Gary notification system — quota thresholds, message queue, popup state
AI service — sends prompts to Claude API, parses JSON, updates NPC state
View
Overworld renderer — tile map, NPC sprites, player, day lighting, night overlay with multiply blend
Encounter renderer — NPC portrait, dialogue box, clipboard UI, Hell Inc. vignette effect
UI overlay — soul counter, suspicion meter, quota progress, Gary notification popups
Loading screen — NPC portrait cutout over door background, GTA 5 style per encounter
Transition handler — manages cut and fade between overworld and encounter view
Controller
Player input — movement in overworld, free text input in encounter view
Trigger handler — detects door/spawn/region overlaps and fires events
Encounter controller — manages conversation turns, calls AI service, applies response to model
Game loop — tick-based updates for NPC routines, suspicion changes, Gary notifications


